====Usage notes====
According to {{w|Zhu Xi}}'s 《詩經集傳》 ''Collected Commentaries on the Classic of Poetry'', there are three kinds of trees named {{zh-l|杞}} in the {{w|Classic of Poetry}}:
* {{lang|zh|「柳屬也。」}} "a kind of willows", i.e. {{taxlink|Salix integra|species}},
* {{lang|zh|「枸檵也。」}} "wolfberry", and
* {{lang|zh|「樹，如樗。一名狗骨。」}} "a tree which resembles the varnish tree [{{taxlink|Ailanthus glandulosa|species}}] and is also named 'dog-bone'," ([https://ctext.org/library.pl?if=en&file=9216&page=34#%E6%9D%9E%E6%A8%B9%E5%A6%82%E6%A8%97%E4%B8%80%E5%90%8D%E7%8B%97%E9%AA%A8]) (though unlikely to be the shrubby {{zh-l|麻黃|ephedra}}).

Legge translated {{zh-l|杞}} as either "willow" or "[[medlar]]".

